The military intelligence subdivision (Ab-I Heer, or Ab-I-H), directed by Kieckebusch 
and assisted by Joachim Canaris, gathered information on Allied troops and military 
units, armaments and strategic plans. The espionage section was made up of subdivi-
sions for air intelligence (Ab-I-Luftwaffe, or Ab-I-L), communications (Ab-I-i-W/T), 
